d, at least temporarily.   The deal created the nation's largest wholesale photofinishingoperation.</TEXT><DATELINE>BRADENTON, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Tropicana Products Inc. has obtained acourt order barring a departed key engineer from divulging ``tradesecrets and secret processes'' to rival Minute Maid.   Tropicana contends when engineer Richard A. Hamilton left lastweek he expressed an ``intense dislike of Tropicana and stated hewould `get' the company.''   Hamilton began work Monday with Minute Maid, a subsidary ofCoca-Cola Foods.</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   NASA officials say two of the three ``moreattractive sites'' for a $1 billion plant to build the nextgeneration of space shuttle rocket boosters are on governmentproperty in Mississippi.   The third is near Cape Canaveral, Fla., where shuttles arelaunched, NASA said Thursday.   NASA officials said they expect a site to be selected beforerequests are issued in June for proposals to build and operate theplant.</TEXT><NOTE>MORE</NOTE></DOC>